                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Mediocre, but careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (only hand b)</seg>
                        <date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of other characters like Michael
                           and Gabrǝʾel (fol. 5r); name of the donor; the word sanbat “Sabbath” on
                           fol. 5v; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 
 Groups of lines on the incipit page of Text II,
                           alternating with black lines; two lines in the incipit of Texts I-1, I-2,
                           I-3 and I-4; of Texts I-3, II and III; two initial lines of sections of
                           Texts I-1, I-3 and I-4.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The scribe wrote on unruled leaves: fols. 33r-35v. - Immediate corrections indicated by thin lines above and below the letter to be cancelled: fols. 20v, 24v.</item>
                     </list>
